script = ExtResource( 1 )
info = "General purpose event manager that is inspired by the one made for Garry's Mod. It was kinda useful at the beginning of project but i've stopped using it that much because locational events covered a lot of cases. Either way, it is still handy so it is going to stay in this project for long.

[c]Usage example[/c]
[gd]
# Add event listener
EventManager.add_event_listener(
	\"character_killed\",
	funcref(self, \"on_character_kill\")
)

# Run event
EventManager.run_event(\"character_killed\", [victim, killer])

# Remove event listener
EventManager.remove_event_listener(
	\"character_killed\",
	funcref(self, \"on_character_kill\")
)
[/gd]

By using a console command called [c]event_manager_list[/c], you can get a list of all available events:
[c]
$ event_manager_list
EventManager available events list:
player_spawn
exit_locked_triggered
exit_unlocked_triggered
character_killed
character_bullet_damage
prop_picked
player_ammo_pickup
on_free_orphan_nodes
character_shooting
...
[/c]"
